The article states that President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has declared the continuation of the national emergency that was initially declared on September 14, 2001, in response to the terrorist attacks on September 11, 2001. This declaration is consistent with section 202(d) of the National Emergencies Act. The reason for the continuation is the ongoing threat of further attacks on the United States. The national emergency and the powers and authorities adopted to address it will remain in effect beyond September 14, 2022, for an additional year. The notice of this continuation will be published in the Federal Register and transmitted to Congress.